        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:36PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 336 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Westplains to over Keota, or
extending from 24 miles northwest of Sterling to 32 miles northwest
of Fort Morgan, moving southeast at 15 mph.  Another strong
thunderstorm was located 15 miles north of Fort Morgan moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Iliff, Stoneham, New Raymer, Pawnee Pass, Willard, Westplains,
Antelope Springs, Logan Corners, Pawnee Buttes, Keota, North
Sterling Reservoir, Padroni and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
